Docker nodes that are not part of a swarm are said to be in single-engine mode.

# To add Docker node on swarm mode:

docker swarm init

# To add a manager to this swarm, run following command:

docker swarm join-token manager

# To check swarm node list:

docker node ls

# To join swarm mode 

docker swarm join --token SWMTKN-1-10piz2kmwyag6co9l8yq0djmzbnqh2rofhnlaayexhs1bpbk4t-6myhjiqunfcq467us14hfm07w 192.168.40.129:2377

When you run docker swarm init command it will show a join link for worker nodes like above.

# To add a manager to this swarm, run the following command:

docker swarm join-token manager

docker swarm join --token ABC-----XYZ 192.168.40.129:2377

docker swarm join-token worker; run following command on docker node to make worker.

To add a worker to this swarm, run the following command:

    docker swarm join --token SWMTKN-1-10piz2kmwyag6co9l8yq0djmzbnqh2rofhnlaayexhs1bpbk4t-6myhjiqunfcq467us14hfm07w 192.168.40.129:2377

# To show Token for Worker Node:

docker swarm join-token -q worker